        "confidence": 0.95,
        "reasoning": "The patch modifies the HashJoinBatchIterator class to fix a subtle bug related to left outer joins missing rows due to hash collisions. The fix involves changing the internal data structure from tracking matched state per hash bucket to tracking matched state per row within each hash bucket. This requires introducing a new HashGroup class with a BitSet to track matched rows individually, changing iteration logic, and adding new iterators for unmatched rows. The changes are deep structural refactorings affecting core join logic and data structures, indicating significant API divergence and complexity beyond simple string or formatting changes. The patch is found with high confidence as an exact match in the target branch, but the complexity of the changes classifies it as TYPE_IV.",
